			<ns0:name>suna...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108616898676203953394/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">What version of the SDK are you using? 0.2.801.0
On what operating system? WinXP x86

&lt;b&gt;What steps will reproduce the problem?&lt;/b&gt;
1. Start HTTP server using python httpd.py 5280
2. Navigate to localhost:5280 
3. Now in Chrome navigate to localhost:5280/?quit=1

What is the expected output? 
HTTP server should quit

What do you see instead?
Nothing happens first time. When you navigate again(Reload), HTTP server quits.

I've seen this happen on WIn7 x64 machine as well but it wasn't consistent. On XP x86 it's consistent.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-06-30T22:06:04.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-04-15T01:14:15.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
